OL,3,CParents of stabbed teenager 'begged'
OL,4,Cpolice to send him to prison, court
OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FA 16-year-old boy from Southwick is on
OL,8,Ftrial at Brighton Crown Court for his
OL,9,Fmurder.
OL,11,FDuring the trial, Mustafa's parents
OL,12,Frevealed how they "begged" police to
OL,13,Fsend their 17-year-old son to prison
OL,14,Fto get him away from drug dealing.
OL,16,FJurors had heard when Mustafa turned
OL,17,F16, things "got worse" and his
OL,18,Fbehaviour changed, his parents found
OL,19,Fweapons in his pockets and he went
OL,20,Fmissing for days on occasion, coming
OL,21,Fback with valuable items or injuries.
