OL,5,Chears
OL,7,FWhen he did come home he had with him
OL,8,Fa "very expensive" bottle of Chanel
OL,9,Fperfume, which he said a friend gave
OL,10,Fhim.
OL,12,F"I was worried he was being exploited
OL,13,Fin some way," Mr Momand said.
OL,15,F"We begged police to put him in
OL,16,Fjuvenile prison.
OL,18,F"I was also thinking he was beginning
OL,19,Fto look like a drug user, he had dirty
OL,20,Fclothes and dirty nails."
